Look for a "Limit", "LOQ", "Reporting Limit", or "<" threshold in the column
header or footnote (e.g. "<0.30 ppm", "LOQ = 0.05 ppm"). Record as page_loq
together with its unit (page_loq_unit). If none stated, set page_loq to 0.

STEP 3 — READ EVERY ELEMENT ROW (report value in the unit AS PRINTED):
1. ACTUAL NUMBER printed (e.g. "1.25", "0.50", "285") → use that exact number,
   and set concentration_unit to the column's unit (could be ppm OR ppb).
2. "<X.XX" or "≤X.XX" → use X.XX as the value, set observed_level to "<X.XX".
3. "BDL (0.034 ppm)" or "BLQ (0.05)" (bracketed limit) → use the bracketed number
   0.034 as the value; set observed_level to the full raw text "BDL (0.034 ppm)".
4. "BDL" / "BLQ" / "Below LOQ" with NO bracketed number → use page_loq if known,
   else 0; set observed_level to the raw text.
5. "ND" / "Not Detected" / "Below LOD" / "<LOD" → value 0.0; observed_level "ND".
6. "NA" / "N/A" / blank / "Not Tested" → value 0.0; observed_level "Not tested".
7. Multiple batch result columns → take the MAXIMUM across batches.
8. Intentionally-added elements → still extract the value, never skip.

ALWAYS set observed_level to the EXACT raw text in the result cell (including the
"<", "BDL", brackets, and any unit). This is the audit trail.

Also extract per-element: intentionally_added (Yes/No), listed_in_coa (Yes/No),
analytical_method (ICP-MS/ICP-OES/AAS), comments (footnotes).

Return ONLY valid JSON — no markdown, no explanation:
{{
  "page_loq": 0.30,
  "page_loq_unit": "ppm",
  "elements": [
    {{
      "symbol": "Pb",
      "name": "Lead",
      "class": "1",
      "concentration_value": 285,
      "concentration_unit": "ppb",
      "observed_level": "285 ppb",
      "analytical_method": "ICP-MS",
      "intentionally_added": "No",
      "listed_in_coa": "Yes",
      "comments": ""
    }}
  ]
}}"""


